parameters:
Come now, our shop is filled with young girls! Please come
and visit!

You still plan to work in the pleasure district even at a
time like this? Ahaha, you've got guts, I'll give you that

Oh!? You're a real beauty, aren't you! Wanna get cozy with
me?

I'm keeping watch to make sure no girls escape from the
pleasure district... You there, you have a face I've not
seen around these parts. Are you new here?

What's this? You came to the pleasure district at a time
like this? As you can see, we're open for business. If
you're here to work, do as you please.

Hehehe...\I[15]It was worth every penny I spent. Alright,
I'll work hard and come back again~

Haa haa...! As expected of Japan's number one pleasure
district. It's filled with beauties

I'm glad the pleasure district is open Now, who shall I get
cozy with tonight?

This pleasure district is the liveliest place in Edo. They
aptly call it the city that never sleeps.

Even if the world is busy, I can't stop visiting the
pleasure quarters. Still, it seems there are fewer people
than before.

Ugh... I want to talk to my favorite girl, but I haven't
received this month's salary yet...

Hmm... Which girl should I choose... It's tough to decide
with so many cute ones...

I feel like running away from Edo with the girl I love. But
I don't have enough money to buy her freedom...
Let's go to Momiji-san's house first.

What's the matter, Karin-san? Aren't you going to escape
from Edo? If that's the case, it can't be helped. You can
continue to use the pleasure quarters' room as you like.

Acts of violence and misconduct in the pleasure district
will be severely punished--
Eh!? Are you the new courtesan?
Yes. Can I pass with this?

Oh! What a splendid courtesan look\I[15] My apologies for
mistaking you for a town girl. Go ahead. If you talk to the
brothel manager on the second floor, you'll be able to start
working.

Thank you very much. I'll head to the second floor of the
brothel.

This area is off-limits to anyone who isn't a client or part
of the brothel's staff. It's no place for a town girl like
you. You don't even have a courtesan's clothes, do you? Go
on, go home--

(It seems I need a Courtesan's Kimono to go beyond this
point...)

I'm not slacking off on the job. It's just a little pick-me-
up. *hic*...

I'm not slacking off on the job. It's just a little pick-me-
up. *hic*...

I'm not slacking off on the job. It's just a little pick-me-
up. *hic*...

I'm not slacking off on the job. It's just a little pick-me-
up. *hic*...

I'm not slacking off on the job. It's just a little pick-me-
up. *hic*...

Even within the pleasure quarters, there's a hierarchy. The
large establishment at the very back is the most
prestigious. Men with money prefer that shop.

Even at times like this, there are those who come to the
pleasure quarters. Perhaps this is the nature of humans.
Ha ha ha! Entertain me tonight as well

(...Those two are going to spend a passionate night
together...)

Master, I've been waiting for you\I[15] Come now, please
head to the second floor~

"Hey! Snatching away my best customer like that! You're
terrible!"?
...I-I'm sorry. I just got carried away...

I heard that the pleasure quarters were unharmed, but the
area around the castle was hit pretty hard.

Heh, once I've saved up some money from work, I'll spend it
at the pleasure quarters or on gambling. That's the style of
a man working in Edo.

Heh heh heh! I hit it big with a gamble, so I'm planning to
spend it all since who knows what tomorrow will bring.

It's been quite a while since I've been to this pleasure
district, having been away from Edo for about a year. Ahh, I
can't wait to see the courtesan I'm familiar with.

The red-light district is quite popular. Some folks even
frequent it with money they've gotten up to no good with.
Well, you can usually tell such scoundrels by their looks.
Oh... I'm not like that, alright!?

The world's already coming to an end. Might as well blow all
my money in the pleasure quarters.

...Oh, are you the new girl? You're cute\I[15]If you're
working today, I'll make sure to request you.

Because I was late to the shop, the girl I was fond of was
taken away by another customer right before my eyes...
*sniffle*...

The red-light district is no place for a town girl. Go back
home.

(This is the top red-light district in Edo... It doesn't
seem like I can enter. I have no business in the pleasure
quarters right now, so I'll try another time.)

From here on is the red-light district--no one but customers
and men are allowed in.

Eh!? I can't enter the red-light district? But I'm looking
for someone, can't I just stay for a little while...?

No way, no way. The comings and goings of women are strictly
controlled here. Without an [Introduction Letter], girls
can't enter. Go home.

(Introduction Letter...? Hmm, I need to find someone
connected to the red-light district...)

Beyond this point is the red-light district--without an
introduction letter, girls can't enter. Go back home.
What? Who gave you this introduction letter?
It's from Oei-san... I mean, from Eiran-tayuu.
Eh!? From Eiran-tayuu...? Show me that introduction letter!
--Karin handed the man the introduction letter.

Hmm... This calligraphy, there's no mistake. It's definitely
Eiran-tayuu's handwriting.

Yes. She was the most popular courtesan in the Edo red-light
district. Almost 20 years ago, she was bought by a patron
for a huge sum of 300 ry. She was a beauty with a
reputation so great, she's considered a legendary courtesan.

Is that so!? (I had no idea... Oei-san was really a
courtesan.)

It says here you want to be allowed to move freely within
the red-light district, is that really okay? This place
might look glamorous, but it can be quite tough, you know?

Yes... please let me enter the red-light district. There's
someone I want to meet here. A person named Momiji-san--

Understood. Then I'll make a special exception and allow you
to enter the red-light district. Momiji-san lives in the
building down to the left. If you want to go further back
into the district, you'll need a courtesan's kimono. Get one
later from Shouemon-san, who manages this red-light
district.

Oh, thank you very much! (Yes! I can finally enter the red-
light district)

--Karin has gained access to enter and leave the red-light
district!

Oh dear... Master, you're coming back late. I hope your wife
doesn't notice you've been lingering at the pleasure
quarters because of your late returns...

That kind of chump change won't do, sir. If you don't have
the money, why not just buy one of the cheap streetwalkers
in town?

Uuu! Please let me see the courtesan with this money! I beg
you, it's my dying wish!

(...I've been to the red-light district many times, but I
still haven't encountered the culprit...)

(Could it be... the culprit isn't a customer? But since I've
come this far, I might as well stick around a little
longer.)
--! (This premonition in my chest...! Could it be...!? )

Hehe... You're just my type I'm counting on you for a good
time.
Ye-yes...! Please, this way to the second floor--
--Karin went upstairs with the nominated client.

Heheh. I always love the atmosphere of the red-light
district no matter when I come \I[15]

Is that so? That's nice to hear. I quite like the glamorous
feel of the red-light district myself.
I haven't seen your face before, are you new here?
Yes. My name is O-Ri. Please remember me--

I've never seen such a fine new courtesan before. Today's my
lucky day
Thank you for the compliment. I'll prepare some drinks now.

No need for tea or booze. I came here to bed a woman. Let's
get you undressed right away.

What's with the scared face? Hurry up and get naked, will
ya?
Understood. Then, please allow me to change.
--Karin transformed into her Mouse Girl form!
What the--!? Who the hell are you...!?

If you're surprised to see this form, it means you know who
I am, right? Show your true self!
Damn it! In such a cramped room--!

Hah! Going for the heart right off the bat shows you're used
to fighting. But too bad, you didn't reach the vital spot.
Kekeke!
...! (Damn it! My attack was too shallow!)

If you're going to transform, then I'll return to my true
form as well! Geha! Gehahaha!

We just met recently, didn't we? One of the War Oni, Lord
Aomaru!

You didn't notice because I was dressed as a courtesan.
Seriously though, why are you working in a red-light
district?

I heard about the courtesan disappearances. To think that
you were the culprit... It's like poking in a bush expecting
a snake and finding a real demon instead.

Hah, not quite. So... what are you gonna do? Fight right
here and now?
Aomaru. Where did you take the courtesans you abducted?

Ah, after bedding them in human disguise, I took them all to
my lair. Once I got bored of playing with them, they all
ended up in my stomach. Gehahaha!

Hey, hey! You seriously wanna fight it out here? Give me a
break. Stuff will get broken. If we're gonna kill each
other, let's do it somewhere else, yeah? I like the red-
light district. Put away your sword, will ya? Eh?
Shut up! I'll exterminate you right here and now!

Tch--! Can't be helped... If you're that eager, then I won't
hold back either!

Didn't I tell you? Stuff will get broken here--more
precisely, it'll burn to ashes! Guhahaha!

(At this rate, it'll end up in flames just like the
bandit fortress did!)

It's too late to panic now! This is what happens when you
don't listen to people's advice. Shall we make the red-light
district even more chaotic? With my flames, that is!

What the hell is this!? A fire!? Everyone, bring water,
bring water--!

...Momiji, huh? You survived too? After you left us, I
thought you had died a stray dog's death...

Yes. It seems you're still in one piece as well. The last
time we spoke was about 30 years ago, wasn't it... Are you
still serving that person?

Hmph... I grew tired of our leader and recently fled just
like you did. Now I'm free. That's why I've been frequenting
the red-light district.

Heh, you've got a face that says you can't believe it? Well,
whatever. If you join the fight, this red-light district
will turn into a sea of fire. I'll back off for now. See
ya--
--! Wait, wait! Where do you think you're running off to?

I'm not running. If you want to fight, come to the old red-
light district that's now a ruin. That's where I'm living
now. Kekeke--!

--Aomaru laughed as he leaped out of the window into the
dark night sky!

Phew... Looks like the fire's out. It was just a small one,
thankfully. If we had fought in the red-light district, the
buildings might have burned down...

He's the culprit? Who would have thought a real demon was
frequenting the red-light district...

Shouemon-san, that demon said he's living in the old red-
light district that has become a ruin. The place is
indeed...

Ah, I think he means the old red-light district that burned
down in the great Edo fire 50 years ago. Surprising that
he's made his home so close by.
Where is this old red-light district located?
This way. Both of you, follow me.
This is... the entrance to the... old red-light district?

Yes, that's right. The door that never opens--that's what
they call it. Because of poison rats and ghosts, it's off-
limits and absolutely no one approaches... truly a forbidden
place.
Understood. Then let's head there ourselves.
Eh--? You intend to fight that demon?

Yes. If we don't, the courtesan disappearances will continue
to occur. Momiji-san, may I ask for your company as well?

Of course, I will accompany you. Aomaru has a very violent
nature. We can't leave him be. When you want to go to the
red-light district ruins, please speak to me.

Understood. I'll return home for today. When it's time to
go, I'll come back here.

Oh!? You came all the way over here for me? Heh, you look
even sexier up close\I[15]

Is your name Karin-chan? I'll remember that. If I get the
chance, I'll make sure to request you

Hmm...? Aren't you... Didn't you used to work at the
dumpling shop? I'm sure it was in the castle town--

--! No! You've got the wrong person! I don't know anything
about a dumpling shop, yes! (Awkward...!)
